Class prime

  • java.lang.Object
    • prime
  • public class prime
extends java.lang.Object

    Find prime numbers

    The prime class takes input form the user for the range and style of output. It then proceeds to evaluate each nubmer for it being a prime or not. Results are returned along with a count of the number of primes found.

      • is_prime

        public static boolean is_prime​(int n)
        Brute force calculation of primes by checking: 1. Is the number 1, 2 or 3? Then it's a prime. 2. Is the number not above? Then check if it's even, if so it's not a prime. 3. The number is now odd. Assume it's a prime. Check to see if it's not prime by modulus division with all odd numbers greater than 1 up to n-1 for 0 remainder. If a zero remainder is found then it's not a prime.
        Parameters:
        n - Number to test.
        Returns:
        boolean Is the number a prime?
